cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper deals with modeling and synthesizing dynamic patterns in video sequences using a spatial-temporal generative ConvNet. The paper focuses on computer vision and machine learning techniques, which are typically covered in the computer science sub-categories of computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), multimedia (cs.MM), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Given the focus on video sequences and ConvNets, cs.CV and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.AI, cs.MM, and cs.NE.
